= Mechanistic Interpretability
Mechanistic interpretability is the study of how neural networks get results.
The leading modules for this way to explain AI is attempting to modeled them as
circuits. I want to not only consider this work but attempt to implement these
abstraction in the model. By iterating this process I believe we can build
better intuition on how LLMs work. In addition, these can make hardware
optimizations better as well as direct hardware implementations. This is based
on Dr Hoeseok Yang's pitch. I have talked with him about what I would like to
do and he has is other ideas.

